{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-readme-js","path":"/sduff/awesome-splunk/readme","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"366740f4-ed08-5f90-9f1b-237613283fa1","html":"<div align=\"center\">\n\t<img width=\"344\" height=\"193\" src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/sduff/awesome-splunk/master/splunk.jpg\" alt=\"Splunk\">\n</div>\n<h1 id=\"awesome-splunk-awesome\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#awesome-splunk-awesome\" aria-label=\"awesome splunk awesome permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Awesome Splunk <a href=\"https://awesome.re\"><img src=\"https://awesome.re/badge.svg\" alt=\"Awesome\"></a></h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p>A curated list of awesome apps, visualisations and other resources for Splunk.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://splunk.com\"><em>Splunk</em></a> captures, indexes, and correlates real-time data in a searchable\nrepository from which graphs, reports, alerts, dashboards, and visualizations\ncan be generated. It is widely used in industries such as finance, utilities,\nhealthcare and manufacturing for use-cases including security, compliance and\nIT service monitoring.</p>\n<h2 id=\"contents\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#contents\" aria-label=\"contents permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Contents</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#basics\">Basics</a> Basic resources for getting started</li>\n<li><a href=\"#apps\">Apps</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#premium-apps\">Premium Apps</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"#visualisations\">Visualisations</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#conferences-meet-ups-and-socialising\">Conferences, Meet-Ups and Socialising</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#unofficial-resources\">Unofficial Resources</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"basics\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#basics\" aria-label=\"basics permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Basics</h2>\n<p>Basic resources for getting started with Splunk.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://splunk.com\">Splunk Website</a> - Splunk's Homepage.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.splunk.com/download\">Downloads</a> - Download page.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.splunk.com/page/previous_releases\">Previous Releases</a> - Previous versions of Splunk Enterprise, Splunk Forwarders.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://answers.splunk.com\">Splunk Answers</a> - Splunk's Community Questions and Answers.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://splunkbase.splunk.com\">SplunkBase</a> - Splunk and Community built apps and add-ons.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blogs.splunk.com/\">Splunk Blogs</a> - Blog posts on various topics.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://dev.splunk.com\">Splunk Dev</a> - Develop on Splunk.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://dev.splunk.com/enterprise/dev_license/\">Free Dev License</a> - Request a free Splunk Developer license.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.splunk.com/\">Splunk Docs</a> - Documentation.</li>\n<li>Splunk Sizing Calculators\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://splunk-sizing.appspot.com/\">Storage</a> - Web Based Storage Requirement Calculator.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"apps\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#apps\" aria-label=\"apps permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Apps</h2>\n<p>Recommended Splunk Apps.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.splunk.com/en_us/software/splunk-enterprise/server-and-infrastructure-monitoring-and-troubleshooting.html\">Splunk App for Infrastructure</a> - Correlate logs and metrics for infrastructure monitoring.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/3975/\">Splunkbase Entry</a> - Download page.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.splunk.com/Documentation/InfraApp\">SAI Documentation</a> - Splunk App for Infrastructure Documentation.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.splunk.com/Documentation/InfraApp/latest/Install/About\">SAI Install Guide</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jimmyatSplunk/SplunkForwarderRepairKit\">Miscellaneous Scripts for fixing issues with the Universal Forwarder</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/jimmyatSplunk/SplunkForwarderRepairKit\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">23</span></span></a> - This kit was compiled based on common issues with Splunk deployments and managing idiosyncrasies that tend to naturally occur.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"premium-apps\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#premium-apps\" aria-label=\"premium apps permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Premium Apps</h3>\n<p>Premium Apps for Splunk.</p>\n<h4 id=\"enterprise-security\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#enterprise-security\" aria-label=\"enterprise security permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Enterprise Security</h4>\n<p>Splunk Enterprise Security is the nerve centre of the security ecosystem, giving teams the insight to quickly detect and respond to internal and external attacks, simplify threat management minimizing risk.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.splunk.com/en_us/software/enterprise-security.html\">ES Home Page</a> - Splunk's Home Page for Enterprise Security.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/263/\">ES Splunkbase Entry</a> - Download page (if licensed).</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.splunk.com/Documentation/ES/latest\">ES Documentation</a> - Splunk documentation for Enterprise Security.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/sduff/awesome-es/\">Awesome-ES</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/sduff/awesome-es/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">12</span></span></a> - An Awesome list for all things Enterprise Security.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"it-service-intelligence\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#it-service-intelligence\" aria-label=\"it service intelligence permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>IT Service Intelligence</h4>\n<p>Splunk IT Service Intelligence (ITSI) is a monitoring and analytics solution powered by artificial intelligence for IT Operations (AIOps) that provides visibility into health and key performance indicators of critical IT and business services, and its infrastructure.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.splunk.com/en_us/software/it-service-intelligence.html\">ITSI Home Page</a> - Splunk's Home Page for IT Service Intelligence.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/1841/\">ITSI Splunkbase Entry</a> - Download page (if licensed).</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.splunk.com/Documentation/ITSI/latest\">ITSI Documentation</a> - ITSI Documentation.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/sduff/awesome-itsi/\">Awesome-ITSI</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/sduff/awesome-itsi/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">13</span></span></a> - An Awesome list for all things IT Service Intelligence.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"visualisations\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#visualisations\" aria-label=\"visualisations permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Visualisations</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/4370/\">Event Timeline Viz</a> - Interactive timeline with call-outs for events.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/3120/\">Timeline</a> - Interactive timeline.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/3514/\">Halo</a> - Hierarchical, relational pie charts.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/4460/\">Heat Map</a> - A grid of related measurements, colour intensity derived from the value.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/3162/\">Calendar Heat Map</a> - Heatmap broken down by days.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/3129/\">Punchcard</a> - Punchcard Visualisation.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/3117/\">Horizon Chart</a> - Horizon Chart Visualisation.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/3112/\">Sankey Diagram</a> - Sankey Diagram Visualisation.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://splunkbase.splunk.com/app/3674/\">WebGL Globe</a> - Spinning globe with events correlated to locations (flashy C-level eye-candy).</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://splunkbase.splunk.com/apps/#/app_content/visualizations\">Splunkbase Custom Visualizations</a> - Download other custom visualizations from Splunkbase.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"conferences-meet-ups-and-socialising\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#conferences-meet-ups-and-socialising\" aria-label=\"conferences meet ups and socialising permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Conferences, Meet-Ups and Socialising</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://usergroups.splunk.com/\">UserGroups</a> - Find a nearby usergroup.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://conf.splunk.com\">.Conf</a> - Splunk's annual conference website.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://conf.splunk.com/watch/conf-online.html\">Past .Conf Material</a> - Watch past presentations and download the slides from past .conf presentations.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://splk.it/slack\">Splunk UserGroups Slack</a> - Splunk's publicly accessible Slack.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://reddit.com/r/splunk\">/r/Splunk</a> - Unofficial Sub-Reddit.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wiki.splunk.com/Community:IRC\">IRC</a> - Instructions for connecting to <code class=\"language-text\">#splunk</code> of Efnet.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.mylogocloud.com/splunk\">Splunk Store</a> - Order some Splunk Schwag you missed from a meetup or .conf.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.splunk.com/en_us/community/splunk-trust.html\">Splunk Trust</a> - The Splunk Trust is an invite only group of Splunk Ninjas.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"unofficial-resources\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#unofficial-resources\" aria-label=\"unofficial resources permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Unofficial Resources</h2>\n<p>Useful Splunk resources that are not specifically associated with Splunk Inc.</p>\n<h4 id=\"personal-home-pages\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#personal-home-pages\" aria-label=\"personal home pages permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Personal Home Pages</h4>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://simonduff.net/splunk\">Simon Duff</a> - Miscellaneous scripts and visualisations.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.rfaircloth.com/\">Ryan Faircloth</a> - Security and Syslog related materials.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.georgestarcher.com/\">George Starcher</a> - Many Splunk related items, including details on Splunk ES's Extreme Search.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://anthonygtellez.github.io/\">Anthony Tellez</a> - Security and Machine Learning items.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.duanewaddle.com/\">Duane Waddle</a> - Miscellaneous Splunk items.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/hire-vladimir/\">Vladimir's GitHub</a> - Code for a number of Splunk resources, including <a href=\"https://github.com/hire-vladimir/SA-cim_vladiator\">CIM Validation</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/hire-vladimir/SA-cim_vladiator\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">65</span></span></a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/nicovdw/\">Nico's GitHub</a> -  Repository of searches and dashboards to assist with optimising concurrency settings.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.davidveuve.com/tech/\">David Veuve</a> - Some early resources on Splunk basics and optimisations (infrequently updated).</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"spl-repositories\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#spl-repositories\" aria-label=\"spl repositories permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>SPL Repositories</h4>\n<p>Collections of useful Splunk searches</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://gosplunk.com/\">GoSplunk</a> - Search Engine for Splunk Queries split by sourcetype and use-case.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"contribute\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#contribute\" aria-label=\"contribute permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Contribute</h2>\n<p>Contributions welcome! Read the <a href=\"https://github.com/sduff/awesome-splunk/blob/master/contributing.md\">contribution guidelines</a> first.</p>\n<h2 id=\"licence\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#licence\" aria-label=\"licence permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Licence</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0\"><img src=\"https://mirrors.creativecommons.org/presskit/buttons/88x31/svg/cc-zero.svg\" alt=\"CC0\"></a></p>\n<p>To the extent possible under law, Simon Duff has waived all copyright and\nrelated or neighbouring rights to this work.</p>","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#awesome-splunk-awesome\">Awesome Splunk <img src=\"https://awesome.re/badge.svg\" alt=\"Awesome\"></a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#contents\">Contents</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#basics\">Basics</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#apps\">Apps</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#premium-apps\">Premium Apps</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#visualisations\">Visualisations</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#conferences-meet-ups-and-socialising\">Conferences, Meet-Ups and Socialising</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#unofficial-resources\">Unofficial Resources</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#contribute\">Contribute</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#licence\">Licence</a></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>","headings":[{"id":"awesome-splunk-awesome","value":"Awesome Splunk Awesome","depth":1},{"id":"contents","value":"Contents","depth":2},{"id":"basics","value":"Basics","depth":2},{"id":"apps","value":"Apps","depth":